<br>
Once the pet is aggro'd on a mob (ie: a taunt or a round of melee to get on the hate list of the mob), the whole 'indifferent pet' doesn't mean anything.  Hate lists will still be passed by the mob who is aggro'd just like normal.  The only difference is that the pet while getting to the mob, or while moving around in the zone would NOT aggro mobs simply because the pet runs past the mob.<br>
<br>
An enchanter's Dire Charm'd pet could follow the same indifferent rule. It would make NO difference than currently (currently, pets are on the faction of the master.  if something is kos to the master, it's kos to the pet. therefore if the ENC could walk deep into a dungeon w/o generating aggro currently, they could do the exact same thing with an indiff pet. if currently the enc would get aggro running deep, whether they have a dire charmed pet or not isn't going to change that).<br>
<br>
There are very few non-social mobs around that you can walk up to and whack while another mob right next to him just watches you.  The VAST majority of mobs in the game are social (at least with other mobs on same faction or of same kind).  The MAIN reason currently people can walk up to 2 mobs and kill one while the other watches is because they are non-kos and have the +10 lvl over the mob.<br>
<br>
Pets running thru lower lvl dungeons and generating lots of aggro from relatively far off mobs is exactly because of the aggro range associated with lvl.  Pulling is ALL about lvl.  As a lvl 60 mage, i pull Village in Velks 10x better than the lvl 56 monk. Why?  Because i have 10+ lvl on most of the mobs there, and i'm smart and always pull the higher of 2 mobs standing side by side to get singles.  Ever watch a +CoV melee killing in Cobalt Scar? They can kill the wyverns while standing right next to another one. Why? because they are not kos to the wyverns and have 10+ lvl's on the one standing there.  Try doing that with the epic pet.  All wyverns in the area will aggro on the pet immediately.<br>
<br>
Do i want to see that part change? Definately not.  Hate lists and how they're passed should not change at all.  The ONLY aspect i want changed is for pets not to aggro mobs when the pet is not currently on any other hate list.<br>
